In General.
We collect several different types of information from you when you use our Services or about you via someone else using our Services (like when a friend adds your email to an event). The information
              received through our Services may be sent to servers located in the United States and other countries around the world. You are not required to provide us with any information, but if you do not provide us with certain
              information, you may be unable to access parts of the Services – for example, if you do not provide your email address, you cannot create an account.
Information you provide.
We collect and store information you enter on our Services or that is provided to us in some other manner. This includes identification information, such as your full name,
                  mailing address (e.g., your event location), email address, images, telephone number, and, if you transact business with us, financial information such as your payment method (credit card number, type, expiration date or
                  other financial information, which is collected and stored by a third-party payment processor and not by us). During and after the registration process, we may also request information about your interests and
                  activities, your gender, your age, your location (such as ZIP code and/or country), other demographic or profile information, or we may ask you to complete a survey or send us a review. Additionally, we may collect and
                  store any information you provide while using any comment or chat features.
Information from Social Network Services (including Facebook).
Our Services allow you to create and/or associate your account on our Services using your Facebook or Google account credentials. If you
                  link our Services with any third-party social networking service, we receive and collect certain information related to or associated with your account with that social networking service. You may have the ability to
                  control what information is shared from these third-party social network services by adjusting the privacy settings on those services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of such third-party services.
Information from other sources.
We also obtain information about you from other users, business partners, contractors, and other third parties, and may add it to our account information or other
                  information we have collected about you. For instance, the most frequent piece of information Evite receives under this section is Guest email addresses or cell phone numbers that are provided by Hosts. Other examples of
                  information we may receive include but are not limited to: updated delivery and address information, purchase history, photographs, and additional demographic and behavioral information. We may combine information collected from
                  other sources with the other information we collected directly from and about you and use such combined information as provided in this Policy.
Information collected automatically.
We automatically receive information from the browser, computer, and device used to access our Services. This information most often includes (without limitation)
                  your IP address, your general geographic location (e.g., city/state), your browser type and language, access times, the content of any undeleted cookies that your browser previously accepted from us (see "Cookies"
                  below), and the referring website address.
Cookies and Similar Technologies.
When you visit our Services or receive an email as part of the Services, we may assign the browser, device, or application from which you access our Services one or more
                  cookies or similar technologies to facilitate access to our Services, personalize your online experience, or otherwise operate our Services. Using a cookie or similar technology, we also may automatically collect
                  information about your online activity on our Services, such as the web pages you visit, the emails you open, the links you click, the searches you conduct on our Services, and other information described in the bullet
                  immediately above. Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies or decide which types of cookies to automatically accept or reject. If you choose to
                  decline cookies or other similar technologies, please note that you may have difficulty signing in and may not be able to use some of the interactive features offered through our Services. We and third-party vendors,
                  including Google, use cookies to report how your ad impressions, other uses of ad services, and interactions with these ad impressions and ad services are related to visits to our Services. To learn more about how to opt
                  out of Google's use of the Google Analytics cookie, visit the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on at
//tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
. We may use other
